The paper deals with the formal verification of software, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of threads and scheduling policies suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions partial-order reduction, which is a technique used in formal verification and model checking, making the sub-categories of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and systems and control (cs.SY) relevant as well.
